key_points: Gabby Petito, a 22-year-old from North Port, Florida, went missing during a cross-country trip with her boyfriend, Brian Laundrie.
Brian Laundrie and the van were located at his family's home in North Port, but he is not cooperating with the investigation.
Legal representatives for Laundrie said the family is 'remaining in the background' and hopes for Gabby's safe return.
Petito's family urges Laundrie to provide information on Gabby's last known location and why he returned alone.
North Port police, along with agencies from Sarasota County to New York and the FBI, are involved in the investigation.
There are no obvious signs of foul play in the van, according to investigators.
Gabby's last known contact with her family was on August 25, during a Facetime call with her mother.
The couple documented their travels on social media, with the last post from Gabby appearing on August 25.
North Port PD has found the van but says there is no definitive information of a crime happening in North Port.
Detectives from Suffolk County Police Department in New York, Petito's hometown, are leading the investigation.
spokespersons: Josh Taylor (with the North Port Police Department)
Steven P. Bertolino, P.C. (from Bertolino Law in Long Island, New York)
